Elmer Robles CASTILLO, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 16988. United States Court of Appeals Ninth Circuit. March 21, 1961. E. R. Williams, Stockton, Cal., for appellant. Laurence E. Dayton, U. S. Atty., John Kaplan, Asst. U. S. Atty., and Charles, W. Getchell, Jr., Asst. U. S. Atty., San, Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before ORR, BARNES, and JERT-BERG, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

We have examined the contentions, made by appellant and find them to be-, without merit.

Judgment affirmed.
